modules.description: This module connects MirageOS network interfaces to flows, enabling packet transmission and reception over virtualized or emulated network devices. It provides functions to write buffers or buffer lists as packets, listen for incoming packets, and manage MAC addresses and device statistics. Concrete use cases include implementing virtual network endpoints in unikernels or bridging network stacks over Xen or QubesOS backends.

This module bridges MirageOS network interfaces with flows, allowing packet transmission and reception over virtualized or emulated network devices. It supports writing buffers as packets, listening for incoming packets, and managing MAC addresses and device statistics. Use it to implement virtual network endpoints in unikernels or bridge network stacks over Xen or QubesOS backends. For example, you can forward packets between a virtual device and a flow or monitor traffic on an emulated NIC.
